text:
A gem hidden in an obscure location in Sungei Kadut. Although they are a chicken rice stall, I decided to try their Kway Chap.

At $20 for 3 pax, I would never expect food of such good quality! The innards and pig skin were braised to the right chewiness and extremely flavourful. I tried the recommended Malaysian style kway teow instead of the usual kway and was pleasantly surprised that it paired well with the ingredients.

Thought I didn't try, the chicken and roast meat looks equally appetising! This is definitely a place that anyone should consider to visit if you are in this ulu area where birds don't even want to lay their eggs.
I drive by it often, but no one knows about this place. Cars can be parked on the roadside. The taste is okay, the black rice here still has some flavor. A light lunch was ok.
